        <mxCell id="addendum_hdr" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#1E293B;strokeColor=#334155;fontSize=13;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#F8FAFC;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=12;arcSize=4;" value="ADDENDUM (same page, below §13 sequence) — PLAN.md §7.6 · §7.7 · §7.8" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="4520" x="40" y="2700" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="box76" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#F1F5F9;strokeColor=#64748B;fontSize=11;fontColor=#111827;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;arcSize=4;" value="§7.6 MAIN COORDINATES ALL SUB-AGENTS — NO MIX-UPS&#10;&#10;• Every task = stable task_id (UUID). Supervisor owns task_board[task_id].&#10;• Each worker is constructed with exactly ONE task_id; its engine slot KV never merges with another task.&#10;• report(…) envelope MUST include task_id → bus row + PG audit line always match.&#10;• Main never ingests raw sub-agent transcripts — only structured fields: status, latest_step, result_summary, artifacts.&#10;• Sub-agents never message each other; all cross-task truth = task_board + Main.&#10;&#10;→ Parallel tasks (e.g. user adds work while r1 runs) = separate task_ids, separate slots; Main merges the board each turn." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="300" width="2200" x="40" y="2755" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="box77" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#EDE9FE;strokeColor=#7C3AED;fontSize=11;fontColor=#111827;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;arcSize=4;" value="§7.7 INTERMEDIATE STEP → USER (sub-agent never speaks)&#10;&#10;Sub-agent only: report(STEP, summary=&quot;user-safe one-liner&quot;)&#10;&#10;PATH A — UI only (default): STEP → bus → Supervisor updates task_board → Transport event{task_step} → client pills / feed. Main silent.&#10;&#10;PATH B — User asks (&quot;status?&quot;): task_board snapshot in Main prompt → Main paraphrases in ONE voice, e.g. &#10;   • &quot;Research is done — I'm still building the PDF.&quot;&#10;   • &quot;That part's finished; still working on the next.&quot;&#10;&#10;PATH C — Optional verbal digest: Notifier + policy (importance + min interval) → synthetic turn → Main says one short line (still from board fields, not raw tools).&#10;&#10;DONE / NEEDS_INFO: same chain — always Main (or notifier→Main) for TTS/chat text." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="360" width="2280" x="2280" y="2755" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="box78" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#ECFDF5;strokeColor=#059669;fontSize=11;fontColor=#111827;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;arcSize=4;" value="§7.8 PDF / HOMEWORK CHAIN (many tools, ONE delegate)&#10;&#10;User: &quot;Make a PDF of these homework Q&amp;A.&quot;&#10;Main: single [DELEGATE capability=productivity goal=…]&#10;Sub-agent internal chain: answer items → assemble doc → render_pdf → upload / attach.&#10;STEP reports: &quot;Draft ready&quot; → &quot;Rendering PDF&quot; (Paths A/B/C above).&#10;DONE: payload artifacts[{kind:pdf, …}] + short summary.&#10;Main (or notifier): &quot;Your PDF is ready&quot; + deliver_file / signed URL tool.&#10;Production: one fat tool homework_to_pdf() — same architecture, fewer internal steps." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="2200" x="40" y="3085" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="flow_mini" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#FFFBEB;strokeColor=#D97706;fontSize=11;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#111827;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;arcSize=4;" value="VISUAL REMINDER — data never goes Sub → User direct&#10;&#10;report(STEP|DONE|NEEDS_INFO) → SIGNAL BUS → SUPERVISOR → task_board → (optional) Main inference → TTS/CHAT → USER&#10;                                    ↘ event{task_step} → CLIENT UI (Path A)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="2280" x="2280" y="3085" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="legend" parent="1" style="rounded=1;fillColor=#F8FAFC;strokeColor=#64748B;fontSize=11;fontColor=#111827;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;arcSize=6;" value="LEGEND — blue=user · cyan=client · orange=supervisor · teal=Main · pink=r1 · amber=p2/tools · indigo=memory · purple=bus/notifier · yellow=tools lane&#10;Above: §13 sequence top→bottom. Below colored boxes: §7.6 coordination, §7.7 STEP→user (UI vs voice), §7.8 PDF chain. Arrows on the sequence = control/data flow between lanes." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="72" width="4520" x="40" y="3320" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
